{"key":"post-13088534","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>13088534</id>\n<content>Use narrow mouth jars for grains.&amp;nbsp; The 90 mm opening on a wide mouth jar is almost double the area of the 70 mm opening on a narrow mouth jar.&amp;nbsp; Your chances of contamination are far less when the opening is just over half the size.&amp;nbsp; It's super easy to pour to the smaller opening.&amp;nbsp; Simply bang the jar on a tire or phone book to break up the grains, and then twist and pour.&amp;nbsp; The grains fall like sand in an hour glass.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>13088559</next>\n<prev>13088497</prev>\n<first>13085749</first>\n<last>13088613</last>\n<when>1282537929</when>\n<utime>08/23/10 07:32 AM</utime>\n</post>"}